585
01:00:15,770 --> 01:00:17,329
without moving.

586
01:00:17,329 --> 01:00:26,329
Allison Nelson, twenty-nine years old and
engaged, a socialite, searching for answers

587
01:00:26,329 --> 01:00:36,630
she needed to know, and Noah Calhoun, the
dreamer, thirty-one, visited by the ghost

588
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:47,619
that had come to dominate his life.

589
01:00:47,619 --> 01:00:52,020
Reunion

590
01:00:52,020 --> 01:00:55,360
Neither one of them moved as they faced each
other.

591
01:00:55,360 --> 01:01:02,549
He hadn’t said anything, his muscles seemed
frozen, and for a second she thought he didn’t

592
01:01:02,549 --> 01:01:08,570
recognize her. Suddenly she felt guilty about
showing up this way, without warning, and

593
01:01:08,570 --> 01:01:13,869
this made it harder. She had thought it would
be easier somehow, that she would know what

594
01:01:13,869 --> 01:01:21,640
to say. But she didn’t. Everything that
