608
01:02:38,900 --> 01:02:45,319
She heard the shock in his voice as he spoke,
and surprising her, it all came together—being

609
01:02:45,319 --> 01:02:51,810
here, seeing him. She felt something twitch
inside, something deep and old, something

610
01:02:51,810 --> 01:02:54,609
that made her dizzy for just a second.

611
01:02:54,609 --> 01:02:59,390
She caught herself fighting for control. She
hadn’t expected this to happen, didn’t

612
01:02:59,390 --> 01:03:07,650
want it to happen. She was engaged now. She
hadn’t come here for this ...yet ...

613
01:03:07,650 --> 01:03:10,829
Yet...

614
01:03:10,829 --> 01:03:19,809
Yet the feeling went on despite herself, and
for a brief moment she felt fifteen again.

615
01:03:19,809 --> 01:03:25,770
Felt as she hadn’t in years, as if all her
dreams could still come true.

616
01:03:25,770 --> 01:03:31,230
Felt as though she’d finally come home.

617
01:03:31,230 --> 01:03:36,780
Without another word they came together, as
if it were the most natural thing in the world,

618
01:03:36,780 --> 01:03:43,750
and he put his arms around her, drawing her
close. They held each other tightly, making

619
01:03:43,750 --> 01:03:49,590
it real, both of them letting the fourteen
years of separation dissolve in the deepening

620
01:03:49,590 --> 01:03:51,579
twilight.

